<DocsLayout title="Terraform — AWS">
  <h1>Terraform — AWS</h1>
  <p>
    The AWS Terraform module provisions a production-ready EncodeSwarmr deployment inside a dedicated VPC with
    optional multi-AZ high availability, Auto Scaling for agents, and managed RDS PostgreSQL.
  </p>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <pre><code>                         ┌─────────────────────────────┐
                         │         Route 53 (optional)  │
                         └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                                        │
                    ┌───────────────────▼───────────────────┐
                    │            VPC  10.0.0.0/16            │
                    │                                        │
                    │   Public Subnets (AZ-a, AZ-b)         │
                    │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐      │
                    │  │  ALB (HTTPS :8080)            │      │
                    │  │  NLB (TCP :9443 — gRPC)       │      │
                    │  └──────────┬───────────────────┘      │
                    │             │                           │
                    │   Private Subnets (AZ-a, AZ-b)         │
                    │  ┌──────────▼──────────┐               │
                    │  │  EC2: Controller-01  │  (AZ-a)      │
                    │  │  EC2: Controller-02  │  (AZ-b, HA)  │
                    │  └──────────┬──────────┘               │
                    │             │                           │
                    │  ┌──────────▼──────────┐               │
                    │  │   RDS PostgreSQL     │               │
                    │  │   (Multi-AZ, HA)     │               │
                    │  └─────────────────────┘               │
                    │                                        │
                    │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐      │
                    │  │  EC2 Auto Scaling Group       │      │
                    │  │  Agent Instances (AZ-a, AZ-b) │      │
                    │  └──────────────────────────────┘      │
                    │                                        │
                    │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐      │
                    │  │  EFS (shared media storage)   │      │
                    │  └──────────────────────────────┘      │
                    └────────────────────────────────────────┘</code></pre>

  <h2>Standard vs HA Deployment</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Standard</th><th>HA</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Controller</td><td>1 × EC2 instance</td><td>2 × EC2 instances (Multi-AZ)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Load Balancer</td><td>ALB + NLB</td><td>ALB + NLB (multi-AZ)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Database</td><td>RDS Single-AZ</td><td>RDS Multi-AZ with standby</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agent scaling</td><td>ASG in single AZ</td><td>ASG across 2 AZs</td></tr>
      <tr><td>EFS</td><td>Standard</td><td>One Zone (or Standard)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NAT Gateway</td><td>1 (single AZ)</td><td>2 (one per AZ)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Terraform 1.6 or later</li>
    <li>AWS CLI configured with credentials (<code>aws configure</code> or environment variables)</li>
    <li>An AWS account with permissions to create VPCs, EC2, RDS, EFS, ALB/NLB, IAM roles, and SSM parameters</li>
    <li>An EC2 key pair (for SSH; SSM Session Manager is preferred and does not require a key pair)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Start</h2>
  <pre><code># 1. Navigate to the AWS Terraform directory
cd deploy/terraform/aws

# 2. Copy and configure variables
cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars
$EDITOR terraform.tfvars

# 3. Initialise Terraform
terraform init

# 4. Preview changes
terraform plan

# 5. Apply
terraform apply</code></pre>

  <h3>Minimal <code>terraform.tfvars</code></h3>
  <pre><code>region               = "us-east-1"
encodeswarmr_version = "1.2.0"

# VPC
vpc_cidr             = "10.0.0.0/16"
availability_zones   = ["us-east-1a", "us-east-1b"]

# Controller
controller_instance_type = "t3.large"

# Agents
agent_instance_type   = "c6i.4xlarge"
agent_min_count       = 1
agent_max_count       = 10
agent_desired_count   = 2

# RDS
db_instance_class  = "db.t3.medium"
db_username        = "encodeswarmr"
db_password        = "changeme-use-secrets-manager"

# Optional: custom domain
# domain_name      = "encode.example.com"
# acm_certificate_arn = "arn:aws:acm:..."</code></pre>

  <h2>HA Deployment</h2>
  <pre><code># terraform.tfvars additions for HA
ha_enabled            = true
controller_count      = 2
db_multi_az           = true
nat_gateway_per_az    = true</code></pre>

  <pre><code>terraform apply -var="ha_enabled=true" -var="controller_count=2"</code></pre>

  <h2>Upgrading</h2>
  <pre><code># Update the version in terraform.tfvars:
encodeswarmr_version = "1.3.0"

# Terraform will replace the EC2 launch template and perform a rolling update
terraform apply</code></pre>
  <p>
    Controller instances are replaced one at a time. The ALB/NLB health checks gate traffic — the old instance is
    only deregistered once the new one is healthy.
  </p>

  <h2>Remote State Setup</h2>
  <p>It is strongly recommended to store Terraform state in S3 with DynamoDB locking for team deployments:</p>
  <pre><code># backend.tf
terraform &#123;
  backend "s3" &#123;
    bucket         = "my-tfstate-bucket"
    key            = "encodeswarmr/aws/terraform.tfstate"
    region         = "us-east-1"
    dynamodb_table = "terraform-locks"
    encrypt        = true
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
  <pre><code># Create the S3 bucket and DynamoDB table (one-time setup)
aws s3api create-bucket --bucket my-tfstate-bucket --region us-east-1
aws dynamodb create-table \
  --table-name terraform-locks \
  --attribute-definitions AttributeName=LockID,AttributeType=S \
  --key-schema AttributeName=LockID,KeyType=HASH \
  --billing-mode PAY_PER_REQUEST</code></pre>

  <h2>Connecting to Instances via SSM</h2>
  <p>All instances have the SSM agent installed. No bastion host or SSH key is required:</p>
  <pre><code># List controller instances
aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --filters "Name=tag:Role,Values=controller" \
  --query "Reservations[].Instances[].InstanceId" \
  --output text

# Open a session
aws ssm start-session --target i-0123456789abcdef0

# Port-forward the web UI to localhost
aws ssm start-session \
  --target i-0123456789abcdef0 \
  --document-name AWS-StartPortForwardingSession \
  --parameters "portNumber=8080,localPortNumber=8080"</code></pre>

  <h2>Cost Estimate</h2>

  <h3>Standard Deployment (us-east-1, approximate)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Spec</th><th>Est. Monthly Cost</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Controller EC2</td><td>1 × t3.large (On-Demand)</td><td>~$60</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agent EC2</td><td>2 × c6i.4xlarge (On-Demand)</td><td>~$550</td></tr>
      <tr><td>RDS PostgreSQL</td><td>db.t3.medium, 20 GB gp3</td><td>~$30</td></tr>
      <tr><td>ALB</td><td>1 load balancer</td><td>~$20</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NLB</td><td>1 load balancer</td><td>~$18</td></tr>
      <tr><td>EFS</td><td>100 GB standard</td><td>~$30</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NAT Gateway</td><td>1</td><td>~$35</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data transfer</td><td>variable</td><td>~$20</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td><strong>~$763/mo</strong></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>HA Deployment (us-east-1, approximate)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Spec</th><th>Est. Monthly Cost</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Controller EC2</td><td>2 × t3.large (On-Demand)</td><td>~$120</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agent EC2</td><td>4 × c6i.4xlarge (On-Demand)</td><td>~$1,100</td></tr>
      <tr><td>RDS PostgreSQL</td><td>db.t3.medium, Multi-AZ</td><td>~$60</td></tr>
      <tr><td>ALB + NLB</td><td>2 load balancers</td><td>~$38</td></tr>
      <tr><td>EFS</td><td>100 GB standard</td><td>~$30</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NAT Gateway</td><td>2 (one per AZ)</td><td>~$70</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data transfer</td><td>variable</td><td>~$40</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td><strong>~$1,458/mo</strong></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>Use Spot instances for agents to reduce costs by 60–80%: set <code>agent_use_spot = true</code> in <code>terraform.tfvars</code>.</p>

  <h2>Cleanup</h2>
  <pre><code># Destroy all resources
terraform destroy

# Destroy but keep the RDS snapshot
terraform destroy -target=aws_db_instance.encodeswarmr \
  --var="db_skip_final_snapshot=false"</code></pre>

  <h2>File Reference</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>File</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>main.tf</code></td><td>Root module — calls sub-modules</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>variables.tf</code></td><td>All input variable declarations</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>outputs.tf</code></td><td>Output values (ALB DNS, instance IDs, etc.)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>terraform.tfvars.example</code></td><td>Example variable values — copy to <code>terraform.tfvars</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/vpc/</code></td><td>VPC, subnets, NAT gateways, route tables</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/controller/</code></td><td>EC2 controller instances, IAM role, launch template</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/agents/</code></td><td>ASG, launch template, scaling policies</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/rds/</code></td><td>RDS instance, subnet group, security group</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/efs/</code></td><td>EFS filesystem, mount targets, access points</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/lb/</code></td><td>ALB (HTTP), NLB (gRPC), target groups, listeners</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>modules/ssm/</code></td><td>SSM Parameter Store entries for secrets</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
